  "translations": {
    "en": "Then the Messenger of Allah (peace be upon him and his family) swooned. Bilal entered, saying: Prayer time -- may Allah have mercy on you. So the Messenger of Allah (peace be upon him and his family) went out and led the people in prayer, and he lightened the prayer. Then he said: Call for Ali ibn Abi Talib and Usama ibn Zayd for me. They came, and he (peace be upon him and his family) put one hand on the shoulder of Ali (peace be upon him) and one hand on Usama. Then he said: Go with me to Fatima. So they went with him until he put his head in her lap. Then al-Hasan and al-Husayn (peace be upon them) wept and screamed, saying: May we sacrifice our selves for your self! May our faces be a shield for yours. So the Messenger of Allah (peace be upon him and his family) said: Who are these, Ali? He said: These are your two sons al-Hasan and al-Husayn. So he embraced them and kissed them both. Al-Hasan (peace be upon him) was weeping more intensely, so he said to him: Stop, Hasan, for you have broken the heart of the Messenger of Allah.",
    "ur": "",
    "tr": "",
    "fa": "",
    "id": "",
    "bn": "",
    "es": "",
    "fr": "",
    "de": "",
    "ru": "",
    "zh": ""
  }
